AUDIO: '&gt;&gt; All right. And then over here is where you would enter the transcript. So notice that you would denote the speaker in square brackets like this. So this is the first speaker. You would get them to say this. Here\'s the second speaker'

[23:51] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'which would say this. And then here we are going back to the first speaker. So let me just leave the transcript at the default. And then over here is where you would select the model. Again there are two different models you can choose'

[24:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'from. There\'s a 1.5 billion parameter model which is smaller and can generate faster. Plus, it can create a longer generation of over 90 minutes. However, the quality would be slightly lower than'

[24:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'this 7 billion parameter model, which is going to be larger and generates slower, but it\'s going to be better quality for me because I do have enough VRAMm. I\'m going to use this 7B version. And then for the attention type, if you have any'

[24:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'one of these methods pre-installed to speed up your generation, you can use that. But I\'m just going to set it to auto for it to autodetect how to accelerate this. Now, this setting is really important. Notice that when you'

[24:42] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'generate this, it basically loads your Vibe Voice model onto your GPU\'s VRAM. And this setting, free memory after generate, if you set that to true, it basically unloads this model from your GPU\'s memory after it generates. This is'

[24:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'good if you only want to generate one output and then do something else. So that would free up your VRAMm for other tasks. However, if you want to generate multiple outputs, then it\'s best to leave this to false so that this model'

[25:09] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'is kept within your VRAM and you don\'t need to load this up again for your subsequent generations. And then for diffusion steps, this is basically how many steps you want the AI model to go through before generating your audio. So'

[25:22] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'in general, the more steps you have, the better quality your generation will be, but it\'s going to be a bit slower. And at a certain point, you\'re going to get diminishing returns. So if you set it to like 40 or 50, that\'s often way too many'

[25:34] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'steps, and you\'re just going to be wasting compute at that point. In contrast, if you set this number to lower, then it\'s going to generate faster, but at the sacrifice of some quality. It seems that the sweet spot'

[25:46] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'here is 20 steps. So let\'s just leave it at that. And then seed is basically the starting point of your generation because there could be almost an infinite amount of generations with your two speakers and this transcript because'

[25:59] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'this is generative AI. And then this seed of 42 is just one of those infinite generations. Now, if you set this seed to fixed and you keep all the settings the same with the same transcript and'

[26:11] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the same voices, you\'re going to get the exact same generation as before. So if you want to get a slightly different generation, you would set this to randomize, which is basically going to randomize the seed. And then cfg'

[26:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'basically controls how literally you want the AI to follow your prompt up here. And then temperature is kind of similar. It determines the randomness or variability of your output. So a lower temperature would make the output more'

[26:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'predictable and consistent, whereas a higher temperature would give it more creativity and diversity. And then top P is kind of a similar thing. A lower value would produce more focused and consistent results, whereas a higher'

[26:51] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'value would introduce more diversity. So feel free to play around with these settings to see how it changes the consistency or expressiveness of your generation. And then one last thing, you can either input your transcript over'

